The paper deals with designing algorithms for geometric or combinatorial optimization problems over uncertain data, which is a common theme in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves probabilistic and statistical analysis, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.DM) and statistical learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses applications related to shape fitting and maintaining extent measures, which could be categorized under computational geometry (cs.CG) and computational science (cs.SI).
